## Maestro project conventions (in addition to Effective Java)

These refine the book for this codebase ‚Äî they do not replace Items 1‚Äì90.

### Style
- **4-space indent** (no tabs); match surrounding module style; no drive-by reformatting
- SLF4J with `{}` placeholders; no `System.out.println` in production or tests

### Layer dependencies
- `parser.model` ‚Äî JDK only (Items 17, 62: pure immutable value objects)
- Code layer infra ‚Äî SLF4J + ANTLR OK; no Kafka
- Application layer ‚Äî Kafka at boundary; **Jackson 3** (`tools.jackson.databind`, not `com.fasterxml.jackson`)
- Operator layer ‚Äî K8s client at boundary; reconcile on domain types

### Public API (SDK / operator)
- Minimal surface (Item 15): expose `StreamModel` and fluent builders ‚Äî not `StreamQueriesBuilder`
- Method names follow Stream Language vocabulary (`from`, `filter`, `to`)

### Canonical patterns in this repo

```java
// Items 1, 17, 34, 64 ‚Äî factories, immutability, enums, interfaces
Expression.and(Literal.string("a"), FieldReferenceExpression.of("status"));

// Item 4 ‚Äî utility class
final class DomainFixtures {
    private DomainFixtures() { }
}

// Item 9 ‚Äî resource management
try (var app = new MaestroApplication(model, configs)) {
    app.start();
}
```
